President Obama, President Pe√±a Nieto of Mexico, and Prime Minister Stephen Harper of Canada met for the North American Leaders Summit in 2014. They discussed their vision for a prosperous and secure future for all three countries and announced initiatives aimed at enhancing competitiveness, expanding opportunities for citizens, and promoting peace, security, and development. Some of the key deliverables include creating a North American Trusted Traveler Program, harmonizing trade data, joint investment and tourism cooperation, creating a North American Transportation Plan, strengthening regulatory cooperation, creating a Trilateral Research, Development and Innovation Council, increasing educational exchanges, promoting trilateral cooperation on women's empowerment and entrepreneurship, holding a North American Energy Ministers Meeting, supporting environmental initiatives, coordinating efforts to combat trafficking and counterfeiting, providing support for disaster response in Central America, increasing energy cooperation in Central America and the Caribbean, and creating an outreach mechanism for stakeholder input.